{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:john.10",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "John 10",
    "summary": "Source text for John 10 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:1",
      "text": "Amen, amen, I say to you: He that entereth not by the door into the sheepfold but climbeth up another way, the same is a thief and a robber.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:2",
      "text": "But he that entereth in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:3",
      "text": "To him the porter openeth: and the sheep hear his voice. And he calleth his own sheep by name and leadeth them out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:4",
      "text": "And when he hath let out his own sheep, he goeth before them: and the sheep follow him, because they know his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:5",
      "text": "But a stranger they follow not, but fly from him, because they know not the voice of strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:6",
      "text": "This proverb Jesus spoke to them. But they understood not what he spoke.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:7",
      "text": "Jesus therefore said to them again: Amen, amen, I say to you, I am the door of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:8",
      "text": "All others, as many as have come, are thieves and robbers: and the sheep heard them not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:9",
      "text": "I am the door. By me, if any man enter in, he shall be saved: and he shall go in and go out, and shall find pastures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:10",
      "text": "The thief cometh not, but for to steal and to kill and to destroy. I am come that they may have life and may have it more abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:11",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd giveth his life for his sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:12",
      "text": "But the hireling and he that is not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, seeth the wolf coming and leaveth the sheep and flieth: and the wolf casteth and scattereth the sheep,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:13",
      "text": "And the hireling flieth, because he is a hireling: and he hath no care for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:14",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd: and I know mine, and mine know me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:15",
      "text": "As the Father knoweth me, and I know the Father: and I lay down my life for my sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:16",
      "text": "And other sheep I have that are not of this fold: them also I must bring. And they shall hear my voice: And there shall be one fold and one shepherd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:17",
      "text": "Therefore doth the Father love me: because I lay down my life, that I may take it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:18",
      "text": "No man taketh it away from me: but I lay it down of myself. And I have power to lay it down: and I have power to take it up again. This commandment have I received of my Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:19",
      "text": "A dissension rose again among the Jews for these words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:20",
      "text": "And many of them said: He hath a devil and is mad. Why hear you him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:21",
      "text": "Others said: These are not the words of one that hath a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:22",
      "text": "And it was the feast of the dedication at Jerusalem: and it was winter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:23",
      "text": "And Jesus walked in the temple, in Solomon's porch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:24",
      "text": "The Jews therefore came round about him and said to him: How long dost thou hold our souls in suspense? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:25",
      "text": "Jesus answered them: I speak to you, and you believe not: the works that I do in the name of my Father, they give testimony of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:26",
      "text": "But you do not believe, because you are not of my sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:27",
      "text": "My sheep hear my voice. And I know them: and they follow me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:28",
      "text": "And I give them life everlasting: and they shall not perish for ever. And no man shall pluck them out of my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:29",
      "text": "That which my Father hath given me is greater than all: and no one can snatch them out of the hand of my Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:30",
      "text": "I and the Father are one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:31",
      "text": "The Jews then took up stones to stone him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:32",
      "text": "Jesus answered them: Many good works I have shewed you from my Father. For which of those works do you stone me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:33",
      "text": "The Jews answered him: For a good work we stone thee not, but for blasphemy: and because that thou. being a, man, makest thyself God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:34",
      "text": "Jesus answered them: Is it not written in your law: I said, you are gods?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:35",
      "text": "If he called them gods to whom the word of God was spoken; and the scripture cannot be broken:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:36",
      "text": "Do you say of him whom the Father hath sanctified and sent into the world: Thou blasphemest; because I said: I am the Son of God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:37",
      "text": "If I do not the works of my Father, believe me not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:38",
      "text": "But if I do, though you will not believe me, believe the works: that you may know and believe that the Father is in me and I in the Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:39",
      "text": "They sought therefore to take him: and he escaped out of their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:40",
      "text": "And he went again beyond the Jordan, into that place where John was baptizing first. And there he abode.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:41",
      "text": "And many resorted to him: and they said: John indeed did no sign.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:john.10.42",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:42",
      "text": "But all things whatsoever John said of this man were true. And many believed n him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
